claim.claim-text:
A method for making a joint implant, the method comprising: a. step [201]: providing a blank with at least one dimension smaller than the implant; and b. step [205]: adding material to the blank so as to form surface detail on the implant, wherein adding material to the block includes at least one of laser sintering and electron beam melting, or
wherein adding material to the block includes adding at least one of a ceramic, a metal and a ceramic-metal composite;
characterized in that the method further comprises step [203]: determining a three-dimensional shape of at least one surface of the joint, and in that step [205] includes adding material to the blank such that at least one surface of the implant is a mirror image of at least one surface of the joint.
